article.headline: Chambers' five 3-pointers lead Bulldogs in rout
article.linkText: Chambers unloads on Stetson in Georgia's win
article.story:
ATHENS, Ga. (AP) -- Sophomore Cori Chambers scored a career-high
26 points, including five 3-pointers, to lead Georgia (No. 16 ESPN/USA Today; No. 18 AP) to a 97-42 rout of Stetson on Monday night.

Freshman Megan Darrah added 17 points for the Lady Bulldogs
(13-4), who snapped Stetson's four-game winning streak.

Jaclyn Piloto led the Hatters (5-6) with seven points.

Georgia put together three runs in the first half that humbled
the Hatters. Georgia scored the first six points, including a
3-pointer by Alexis Kendrick.

Piloto hit a jumper to trail 17-9 with 13:08 left in the half.
But the Lady Bulldogs went on a 12-0 run behind Chambers' two
jumpers and a pair of free throws for a 29-9 lead.

Georgia went on another 12-0 run to end the half with a 51-17
advantage. Jessica Pierce hit a pair of spinning jumpers and two
free throws during the spree.

Early in the second half, Georgia outscored the Hatters 14-0 in
four minutes. Darrah's layup off a steal gave the Lady Bulldogs a
50-point lead, 71-21, with 14:06 left.

Stetson shot 30 percent and committed 26 turnovers. Georgia had
seven turnovers.
